# AlgoFlow — Landing Page Context

## What is AlgoFlow?

- **Product:** Interactive algorithm visualizer for learning DSA
- **Tagline:** "Step through algorithms, not just read about them."
- **Audience:** CS students, interview prep, educators
- **Value:** Free, open-source, no signup — 25 algorithms with step-by-step playback

---

## Key Features (for hero, features section, etc.)

- Step-by-step playback — scrub forward/backward through every state
- 25 algorithms across 4 categories
- Code panel — pseudocode synced to current step
- Side-by-side compare — run two algorithms at once
- Big-O reference — time/space complexity cheat sheet
- Custom input — test with your own data
- Practice links — LeetCode, HackerRank, NeetCode
- i18n (en/pt), light/dark theme

---

## Routes

- `/` — Home (category cards)
- `/visualizer/[category]` — Algorithm list per category
- `/visualizer/[category]/[slug]` — Individual visualizer
- `/reference` — Big-O cheat sheet
- `/big-o` — Big-O guide with growth curves
- `/compare` — Side-by-side comparison

---

## Design System

- **Colors:** Use `var(--bg)`, `var(--text)`, `var(--text-muted)`, `var(--border)`, `var(--shadow-md)` — never hardcode
- **Fonts:** `var(--font-display)` headings, `var(--font-body)` body, `var(--font-mono)` code/stats
- **Layout:** Max width 1100px, main has `margin-left: 220px` (sidebar)
- **Logo:** "Algo**F**l**o**w" — F/l/o/w use category colors

---

## i18n

- Always use `t()` from `useI18n()` for user-facing text
- Keys in `public/locales/{en,pt}/` — add new strings to both

---

## Current Homepage Structure

- Header: title, stats (X categories · Y algorithms), search button (⌘K)
- Category cards: grid of 4, link to `/visualizer/{category}`
- SearchOverlay: modal for quick algorithm search
